        "title": "fix(memory): compact short-term promotion entries",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Bound visible short-term promotion snippets before appending them to root `MEMORY.md`, so long daily-note ranges cannot be copied wholesale into bootstrap memory.\n- Add `dreaming.phases.deep.maxPromotedSnippetTokens` (default 120 estimated tokens) and pass it through config, CLI/status, and apply-time promotion.\n- Preserve visible provenance metadata on each promoted entry: `score`, `recalls`, `avg`, and `source`, while keeping marker comments focused on duplicate reconciliation.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- `pnpm exec vitest run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-memory.config.ts extensions/memory-core/src/short-term-promotion.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/config.test.ts`\n- Result: 106 tests passed.\n\n## Notes\nThis is a narrow mitigation, not full semantic long-term-memory curation. The current path is deterministic ranking + rehydration + formatting; it does not ask an LLM to distill stable conclusions for `MEMORY.md`. A follow-up should add an explicit LLM/curator stage for durable-memory promotion rather than relying on snippet compaction alone.\n",
